I tried to upgrade from the Batik version that comes with Apache FOP 0.20.5rc3a 
with latest release Batik 1.5 library but get the following exception when 
running my application:

[code]
java.lang.NullPointerException
	at org.apache.batik.svggen.SVGGeneratorContext.doubleString(Unknown 
Source)
	at org.apache.batik.svggen.SVGGraphics2D.drawString(Unknown Source)
	at org.jfree.chart.TextTitle.drawHorizontal(Unknown Source)
	at org.jfree.chart.TextTitle.draw(Unknown Source)
	at org.jfree.chart.JFreeChart.drawTitle(Unknown Source)
	at org.jfree.chart.JFreeChart.draw(Unknown Source)
	at JFreeChartGenerator.saveChartToSVG(JFreeChartGenerator.java:105)
[/code]

with saveChartToSVG() is:

[code]
    /**
     * Save chart as SVG file.
     * Required libs: Apache Batik
     * 
     * @param chart JFreeChart to save.
     * @param fileName Name of file to save chart in.
     * @param width Width of chart graphic.
     * @param height Height of chart graphic.
     * @throws Exception if failed.
     */
    public void saveChartToSVG(JFreeChart chart, String fileName, int width, 
int height) throws Exception {
        if (chart != null) {
            if (fileName == null) {
                fileName = "chart.svg";
            }
            DOMImplementation domImpl = 
GenericDOMImplementation.getDOMImplementation();
            Document document = domImpl.createDocument(null, "svg", null);
            SVGGraphics2D svgGenerator = new SVGGraphics2D(document);
            chart.draw(svgGenerator, new Rectangle2D.Double(0, 0, width, 
height), null);

            boolean useCSS = true;
                Writer out = new OutputStreamWriter(new FileOutputStream(new 
File(fileName)),"UTF-8");
                svgGenerator.stream(out, useCSS);
                logger.fine("Chart written to "+fileName);
        }
    }//saveChartToSVG()
[/code]

using the batik version that comes with Apache FOP (0.20.5.rc3a) this error 
does not occur.
